<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-732-026  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 732 026.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 2 1989 v6 n39 p25(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bridge speeds communication for VAX, parallel processors.andO;(Paracom's BBK-DR11)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Patch, Kimberly.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Paracom Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Paracom BBK-DR11 (Computer communications equipment) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionTransputersCommunications Boards-CardsBridges (Connector).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Bridge Speeds Communication For VAX, Parallel ProcessorsandM;WEST CHICAGO, Ill.andP;  -- Paracom has announced a bridge that lets VAXescommunicate more quickly with parallel processing machines that containTransputer chips, company officials said.andM;The BBK-DR11 bus bridge uses Inmos' T222 Transputer RISC chip with 32KB of35-nanosecond memory and four communications channels for throughput speedsup to 4Mb per second, said Paracom Vice President Reinhardt Rinn.andM;&quot;The board is hosted on the parallel processing system, and we connect thatto another DR11 interface in the VAX, and then you can send data very fast,&quot;Rinn said.andP;  &quot;You can use the parallel processor as a large performance toolfor a VAX workstation.&quot;andM;Because memory for the bridge is on the Transputer chip, the memory and theprocessor can communicate intantaneously, with no extra bus link, Rinn said.andM;Also contributing to the throughput speed is a chip timing scheme thatautomatically synchronizes accesses to the Dr11 port, which permits thebridge to use a block-move operation to transfer data between the parallelport and links, Rinn said.andM;An optional 16KB of EPROM can accommodate applications that require automaticboot-up.andM;The bridge can be used to connect any computer using a DR11 interface to anyparallel processor that uses the 32-bit Transputer chips.andP;  It supports theHelios distributed operating system, the MultiTool development environment,and C, Occam, Fortran, Pascal, Par.C, Parallel Prolog and Modula-2 compilers.andM;The BBK-DR11 board also doubles as a DR11-compatible 16-bit I/O port tostand-alone parallel processing systems.andM;The BBK-DR11 is priced at $2,345 and is available now.andM;Paracom's Multicluster and Supercluster array processors range from one to 64transputer nodes and vary in price from $1,525 to $400,000.andM;Paracom Inc. is located at 245 W. Roosevelt Road, Building 9, Unit 60, WestChicago, IL 60185, (312) 293-9500.andO;</TEXT></DOC>